column4: <content>[recto] Ad [Addendum] Alchemist Warb.Inst. ""Alchemy"" 1) Frinks (?) pinxit Abrahamus Jacobus sculpsit, [monogram van Cornelis Visscher excudit with 4 lines in Dutch & French Onmogelijck Wie heeft oijt sien wonder rijck [...] Shows woman sitting with book and versions alchemist & instruments behind her a negro (devil ? and in background man working on fire; [verso] Pieter van der Borcht: Monkeys as Alchemists - all figures monkeys, but otherwise very similar to Bruegel and in background view of the poor monkey alchemist family arriving at a house where they are welcomed. There is clearly a connection between to this print. Ex. C. Veth, Geschiedenis van de Nederlandsche Caricaturen, Leiden, 1921, p. 113.</content>
